{"ts": "2026-06-12T00:13:43.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 356, "tokens_out": 505, "elapsed_ms": 5251, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a complete 4-page website for a fictional design agency called \"Forma Studio\". The pages are: Home, About, Work (portfolio grid), and Contact. Each page must be a separate HTML file sharing one style.css and one app.js.\n\nWork can be done in parallel across pages, but all pages must share the same visual language: color palette, typography, spacing, component styles. The design system must be defined first and respected by all page builders.\n\nDeliver: home.html, about.html, work.html, contact.html, style.css, app.js, and a report.md explaining design decisions and how consistency was maintained across parallel work.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T00:13:59.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1319, "tokens_out": 952, "elapsed_ms": 15152, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"design-system\",\n      \"description\": \"Define the design system in style.css and document it in report.md. Specify color palette, typography (fonts, sizes, line heights), spacing scale, button styles, and layout grid. Ensure all components are reusable and consistent across pages.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"home-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create home.html as the main entry page. Include a hero section, agency introduction, featured work preview, and links to About, Work, and Contact pages. Link to shared style.css and app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"about-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create about.html with sections for studio story, team members, and design philosophy. Include navigation linking to home.html, work.html, and contact.html. Use consistent styles from style.css.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"work-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create work.html displaying a responsive portfolio grid of at least 6 fictional projects. Each item should have a thumbnail, title, and category. Ensure layout matches design system. Link to other pages and use shared assets.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"contact-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Create contact.html with a contact form (name, email, message), studio address, and social links. Include consistent navigation and styling from style.css. Ensure form has basic JS validation in app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"js-behavior\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement shared interactivity in app.js: mobile menu toggle, smooth scrolling, and form validation for contact.html. Ensure script works across all HTML pages without errors.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"report\",\n      \"description\": \"Complete report.md explaining design decisions (color, typography, layout), how the design system ensures consistency, and how parallel development was coordinated using shared style.css and app.js.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
